caption: The food is very ok, nothing stands out as exceptional but its not bad either, I'd give it a 3/5 for the food alone. The real winner here is the charm of the place amidst a sea of bland options or hipster dives that populate Bushwick. Its lovely, with solid music choices that fit the atmosphere and the ambiance makes up for what is an otherwise superlative-lacking experience.  Service feels French in that there is a lack of attention to diners, which can be a positive if you want to post up with a book, or a negative if you have alot of demands for brunch. Servers are friendly but put no effort to refill coffee or drinks, take away finished plates, or check-in in a timely manner. It didn't affect my experience much but bad service at least feels on brand in a French bistro.  Hopefully more places like this will open in the area, the vibe and pleasantness of being there outweighs some of the lackluster aspects.
I admire this venue a lot. theres a happy feeling. The food is wonderful. the service is dynamic and the waiters are well trained. The pay is honest. greatly recommend.

Servers could be nicer, we asked for sanitizer and were ignored, also asked to be seated outside and were met with a pretty bad attitude. The food was good and the backyard perfect for a spring/summer day.
Excellent casual French bistro!
Loved the food and service! Amazing pancakes!!😍😍😍
Go for the oysters. Nice outdoor seating. Get the oysters and sit in the backyard on a summer day with a shandy. You won’t regret it!
A French Bistro reminiscent of Restaurant Florent!
Great brunch and very friendly staff
The place serves large dishes and for fair rates. helpful employees. Great work.
Restaurant looked really unkept, food wasn’t great. Our server looked tainted and that’s unprofessional. He was very polite though and attentive but the  environment just wasn’t right !
I really enjoy their dishes. I always get awesome customer service there. The place is well organised and the workers are always very nice. Highly recommended.
One of my main spots to grab something to eat. fantastic location, always clean, and very good customer service. A must try!
Phone number is disconnected. Website doesn't have any info. But looks closed.  Local French bistro. Super homey and super delicious. Just moved to the area and this is one of my new favorites!

Such a wonderful and authentic French restaurant. We loved the ambiance and the cheese plates, and, well, all of the food! When they open back up please go check them out, give them your business, and keep them alive. They're worth it.
Great brunch!
Certainly a spot worth visiting, the food is fantastic and fresh, the prices are fair and it is constantly clean there. 5 stars.
Backyard space has the vibes
highly recommend the rose spritz 😘 brunch was delicious.

What a great restaurant. It had a great ambience. I started off with artichoke and garlic sauce. The sauce was very tasty. I had the Beef Bourguignon. It was very good. The sauce was great. I would highly recommend this restaurant. The service was great and friendly.

This place so wonderful and if I could I would give it  6/5 stars. I come here every now and then when I need to be sure I’ll enjoy the atmosphere and food. Y’all are so lovely and all the food is delicious

Very elegant and welcoming place. They serve large meals and for affordable prices. I enjoyed the food very much and the staff were super personal and explanatory. Will definitely recommend this restaurant.
Great service food and atmosphere

Great vibe for Sunday brunch. Old school classics in the background and a very laid back vibe. All the doors are open, which is great for covid, but do wrap up on cold days as even if seated inside it gets chilly

Ordered 4 entree brunch items from them for delivery. Only received 3 and upon calling them was told by the manager “they would have to believe me when I said there is a missing item”. Have been a customer for a long time mostly in person. Never again. Learn to handle a service issue with some sort of competence. I didn’t need them to bend over backwards, everyone makes mistakes. A simple sorry and how can we make it better would have sufficed. To be accused of possibly taking advantage of them is ridiculous. Worst of all they said to handle it with door dash. Door dash didn’t make the mistake you guys did so own it and learn from it!!!

Amazing service! A hidden Bushwick gem serving $1 oysters all day every day. Wines pair perfect with food menu. Our server Jason was excellent showing us great hospitality, attentiveness, and knowledgeable of menu. Will definitely go again! Highly Recommended.

This place is so cute!!! I quaint french restaurant has seating in the front, a few tables inside and a back yard seating.  The wild mushroom pesto linguine was delicious. My friend got the beef bourguignon looked amazing, however I didn't try it. But, my friend really liked it and has had it a few times before.  We also got the escargot appetizer, but I forgot to take a picture of it. Delicious!!!  It wasn't crazy expensive so I will definitely be back to this restaurant. It's a great place to go for a date. Or just meet a friend for a casual dinner.
Staff is really nice and accommodating. I had the Mominette burger which was good but the fries were a bit over fried but still edible with ketchup.
Great brunch experience
Good old fashioned French classics with American twists. You get what you expect if you're familiar with French eating.  The cocktails are also great. One of my favorite chicken sandwiches in nyc.
This place has amazing service as well as tasty meals. One of the best restaurant around town. The food arrived quickly and the rates were fair. I recommend this place.
The ambiance, staff, escargot, and steak frites are on point. Amen.

I call this superb place often because I enjoy the special air that is exist in this restaurant. The crew is very welcoming and professional. The service is exceptionally quick. Needless to say, the food you get is excellent. I came many times and I was never disappointed. The expense is fair. I suggest this restaurant to to all.
Amazing. So pretty. Food is amazing. Extra star for Gato the cat.

Not authentic. They have a really adorable back area for seating but the music was really quite loud for the morning and it wasn’t French music ;) it was American pop techno... Food was disappointed and expensive. Fries were $7 and extremely greasy and soggy. Basically had eggs and a $45 bill.
Fantastic and fresh food, I loved the vibes this place has, and the staff members were very kind. Will surely eat here again.

My favorite place....
They offer a fantastic variety of delicious food. I loved dining here. Employees are always welcoming, rates are affordable and the place is always well organised.

Very long wait. We were told to wait 20 minute for garden and it ended up over an hour and we still didnt get in the garden. We were starving, so we ordered we thought drinks will be on the place, but ended up they only covered the coffee. Though they brought us initial bill without drinks, but than we got charged for bloody marries in follow up bill. Food was good, but considering the wait of hour + when initially telling us 20 minutes, and than still charging us for drinks while we sit by the road side, and never getting to see a garden. Lets just say, it wasn't a good experience all in all as quality of food didnt make up for incorrect time expectations, and we still didn't get to the garden.
Loved the food. The place is Nice and Cozy. The staff was attentive.
I eat here a lot since I work in the area. I love how the service is always fantastic and they keep the spot neat consistently. Prices are affordable and they serve large portions.

This restaurant is my number one site.  Of all restaurants I know I favor it most. I always suggests to my friends to go to visit this restaurant. Whenever  I I need a fair supper, this is the place that comes immediately to my head. excellent and varied  food and a large menu.generous crew, and pleasant atmosphere. Also, the tariff is affordable. I recommend this place with great pleasure.
Food and drinks here are amazing! Everything I've tried has been delicious. I recommend the chicken and waffles or french toast with any cocktail.

I meet with friends this lovely place from time to time! This is my favorite place to have a bite.  I go there frequently. The meals are of high quality, the staff is welcoming and the price is good. I like meeting in this restaurant over a nice supper.

I’ve always had a great meal and a great experience at Mominette. I’ve had brunch and dinner and both were delicious. In the summer their backyard is beautiful and they even have a jazz band playing out there sometimes. It’s definitely a Bushwick gem!
The place is wonderful and broad, the meals was yummy and the prices were very fair. fast, efficient service and very amiable staff. I highly recommend this place.
I actually loved their dishes and service, excellent location close to my house. The employees are always kind. Will come visit again.
Good burgers, nothing special but certainly solid, interior is really chill and interesting, friendly service too
Chillin...

I meet friends in this nice place often! This is the best place to grab a bite.  I visit this place many times. The meals are just great, the crew is polite and the payment is decent. I like going in this spot over a tasty supper.

Wonderful food, beautiful outside courtyard, great service and $1 oysters, definitely the best restaurant I've been to in Bushwick  *updated* lived in this neighbourhood for three years now, and still had nothing it excellent meals and service here. A local gem

Mominette is a really great deviation from the casual dining spots you typically find around this part of Bushwick. Vibe like your usual French spot. Very cute and small with dim mood lighting. Good for dates or small groups, bad for children/larger groups. The menu is also what you'd expect from a decent French bistro, with a few interesting additions. I had the skate fish, which I hardly ever see despite how easy they are to catch locally. It was delicious. The escargot was decent and the french onion soup was great.
Quiet place, great date night spot
Their french onion soup was great
Always saying hiring. Never interview blacks
We had a fabulous brunch today -food was excellent- service was outstanding  -friendly and attentive- we will definitely be back when in the area- cozy - comfortable environment- lovely hostess
This spot obviously knows how to satisfy their customers. Regularly with a very welcoming demeanor. The food is conveniently priced, regularly delicious and neat.
Great oyster and drinks happy hour.
Used to be a great spot. Not anymore. Plenty of great restraounts nearby.

This 5 stars is for food only. The duck hash was incredible, very well executed. My husband had the Norwegian Benedict and commented that it was the best benedict he’d ever had.  Super excited to come back and try the dinner menu. On  another note, the ambiance was cold and unfriendly. Metal straws have got to go...yuck! They change the entire flavor profile of a drink, and not in a good way. The fruit used in our drinks was clearly left over from the night before...not fresh by any stretch of the imagination. We were grossed out it was in our drinks to begin with. Leave out the fruit entirely if it’s dry and badly oxidized, FYI. *eye roll*

Went for brunch basic American brunch menu. Nothing adventurous.

Brilliant spot for a great lunch . Brilliant food if in the area this is great place to visit and enjoy some brilliant food

I’ve always had a great meal and a great experience at Mominette. I’ve had brunch and dinner and both were delicious. In the summer their backyard is beautiful and they even have a jazz band playing out there sometimes. It’s definitely a Bushwick gem!

I adore this spot! They serve decent food, their menu is decent, The chef in that restaurant is an expert, I enjoy very much eating all their food. The food is consistently of high class, the attitude towards the visitors  is nice. I  go often to this place and I not even once was unhappy.  I highly recommend it.
Great little brunch spot

The escargot stole the show. The cheese plate is disappointing which was really sad given it’s a French place.  The house sparkling has that classic California buttery Chardonnay feel. The cocktails are interesting… Tabasco salt rim.  There’s better French food in town, but this is not pretentious and is definitely worth a visit.

The past two times I went here I was so happy and satisfied that I decided to host my wedding dinner for 12 people here. I called three times before someone picked up. The server told me I shouldn't have my dinner at 5 because that's when they open. I have been a line cook for 7 years in NYC and im Fully aware that the kitchen should be prepared upon service starting even if there is a party of 12.After mentioning I wanted a pre fixe menu he then told me I had to email tyler the manager who never got back to me. I called again and a new sever said she'd give tyler my contact info and he has yet to call me. I made a reservation somewhere else. That was an EASY 1500 dollar you could have made in one night but clearly mominette is too good for my money

This is the best spot in Bushwick. I've never had Norwegian eggs Benedict before and it was DELICIOUS. They had mimosa's by the pitcher and a good set of options. The wife had french toast that was covered in fruit and amazing.  They're cash forward and pass the cc fees onto the customer but whatever.
Good food, beautiful outdoor seating, good service.  I just don't like the additional charge to pay with a debit card, since that's how most people pay nowadays.
Comfortable. Friendly service. Nice crispy potatoes! Warning to visitors: If you use a card you will be charged 2.5% extra on transactions.

The salmon tartar was fresh, yet unmemorable. the mussels were mediocre. The seafood pasta was also so-so. The prize goes to the home made potato chips. Absolutely delicious.

One of my favorite places in the neighbourhood and in NY. The mussels are delicious and so are the oysters. And it is not expensive for what you get. Very good spot to go when the weather is nice because they have a good backyard.

The reward was a pretty lush plate of Eggs Benedict wit buttery, roasted red potatoes and a side of mesclun greens with what sermed to be a dinon mustard vinaigrette. Perfect balnce of flavors really!! Instead of ham, I opted for the bacon and was pleasantly satisfied with the crispy, thick pieces. I see what all the fuss is about ! For $13 this is epic! Mominette Bistro is a great place to tantalize your taste buds and it looks like the cocktails at $9-10 might be the perfect addition on a lazy Saturday or Sunday or whenever! Oh I am returning but I may need to eat more items on that menu..Highly recommend you do the same!
Great food and atmosphere. My only small complaint is the coffee was not flowing as quickly as desired.
I love the onion soup!

I told the waiter, and he came back to ask me if the fries would be better off in the trash. I don’t want to waste food but also not paying for the staff’s lunch. Came at the end of brunch service and food was not good. It didn’t help the situation. Been there several times in the past. Will absolutely never go back. Never.

This spot is the one I like best. I eat in plenty of restaurants but to this restaurant I go the most. The crew is very friendly and the cooking they cook is so flavorful. I would always prefer to have a nice meal here. Highly recommended.

Mominette was one of my favorite restaurants when I lived in Bushwick! The roasted potatoes at brunch are amazing! Great food & customer service!

The food was okay but wasn’t good enough to make up for the terrible circumstances. Will not be returning.
One of my preferred spots to grab something to eat. awesome location, always clean, and fantastic service. A must try!
Food was fabulous!!!

Delicious plates. Awesome service. Beautiful and romantic interior. On street metered parking is hard to find during normal business hours. Call ahead for hours and reservations on busy nights like Friday and Saturday. Definitely recommend you try this spot. 🌻

Good brunch at a reasonable price. Quick table service.

Food is average for a place like this. Yet the prices are high for the neighborhood. Service is really bad and it wasn't even crowded when I went there. The actual place looks much much worse than the photos on maps.

I adore this restaurant! They serve high quality meals, their menu is varied, The chef in that place is a real authority in the kitchen, I love a lot eating all their food. This is a great restaurant. Excellent cocktails, and the food is outstanding!Amazing Lobster Benedict, delicious grass fed burger with goat cheeses and salad!Also the new cocktail, I had the ginger fizz which was lovely! Everything on the menu looked amazing!!! I loved this atmosphere and this spot !! I would definitely like to come back to experience the dinner menu!
Not what it used to be.

Ask for outdoor seating. It’s beautiful. We weren’t able to sit outside. Food is delicious. Loved their cheese sampler and gnocchi. Must try creme brûlée for desert. Over all a good experience and lovely staff.
Great brunch.  Staff was accommodating and friendly.  Food was good too.  Recommend highly.
Would surely recommend trying this place. Exceptional atmosphere, delicious food, fantastic service. Fantastic work.

Such a cute place for happy hour! Loved the dollar oyster special. The glasses of wine were filled and the atmosphere is lovely. Definitely recommend for a laid back after work happy hour!
Super folded eggs, breast chicken and waffles

(Translated by Google) Perfect place! Waiter speaking all French, we came to brunch and everything was great. Excellent Benedict and Norwegian eggs, toasts to avocado too, but think of at least adding a top topping for more taste. The frenchs toast were also excellent. In short, to do absolutely if you are in the neighborhood!  (Original) Endroit parfait ! Serveur parlant tous français, nous sommes venus bruncher et tout était super. Les œufs Bénédict et norvégiens excellents, les toasts a l'avocat également, mais penser a au moins rajouter un toping dessus pour plus de goût. Les frenchs toast (pain perdu)  étaient également excellents. Bref a faire absolument si vous êtes dans le quartier !

This was my go to in bushwick. I absolutely love this restaurant. Their vibe, food, and service is delicious are unparalleled in the neighborhood. No matter the time of day they are always willing to squeeze in your party. The oysters are fresh, the duck breast is amazing, and the cocktails/wine make for an enchanting evening. The garden itself is a beautiful spot for a birthday, a date, or just a Tuesday night. I sincerely love this staff and thank you for the lifelong memories I will have from the service I have received under your roof.

Really great gem of a place. Super neighborhoody and cosy sort of vibe. Had the two sets of mussels and both were fantastic!. Really excellent fries! Just wish there was some bread to mop up the equally excellent broth! Well priced and well worth a visit if you're in the area!
Bad food
The food is delicious! And they have great customer service.
Smelling bath room

When I first moved to Bushwick this place was great. Soon I saw changes in the menu, the chef, and then finally managment or new owner seemed to really simplify the menu. This place used to have really nice burgers a frys as well as tartar and other great dishes and great brunch. So much we came here for New Years eve and other holidays and also took out of town guests here. That was when the menu was on paper.. now its in a dinner style plastic sleeve with cheesy clip art. And the food tastes just as good as the menu. Don't get me wrong.. the food is edible but I wouldnt label it as a French Bistro anymore. Last time I went was a month ago - we agreed to never go back.

So many good things to say about this place. Once you step through the doors it's like you've stepped into a quaint local restaurant in France. Every dish I've ever tried here is so delicious and savory. Not to mention the staff is friendly and attentive but not overbearing. I'd recommend this place for a romantic dinner or wine and oysters with friends.

I LOVE their brunch/ lunch. Their omelettes are amazing. The only reason I have to take a star is because there was random avocado at the bottom of my salad and I am allergic. 😩 I'll still be back though!
Great all around experience.  Lovely setting, food and service.  Nice back area with garden feel.

Mominette is a great local bar and restaurant.  It's usually open for lunch which I love because they serve omelettes on their lunch menu. I don't eat oysters but my date got some 1$ oysters and enjoyed. Also, a super cute spot for brunch. They have a back garden that isn't open for food service so I've never been but I'm sure is very nice.  Service is very friendly and prompt
Very relaxed atmosphere. Everything from the appetizer down to the desert is delicious
Excellent seafood,  yummy Sangrias! 😀
Love this place. Last time we came,  the backyard was closed unfortunately but when we can we always go to the backyard. I had the burger and my husband had the steak and eggs. All was delish!
Great food, nice service, wish there was AC and a lock on the women's bathroom door.

Food was delicious. My only gripe is the syrup was not real syrup (definitely tasted like the corn syrup Aunt Jemima one), and the iced coffee also tasted like yesterdays batch thrown in the fridge. I'd skip the coffee. Otherwise the food was outstanding.
Service was great. Steak was served well done, although I ordered it medium.

Service extremely slow - we arrived at 8.pm and didn’t eat until 9.30. We ordered mussels and they smelled and tasted fishy so we sent them back. The restaurant continued to serve stinky mussels to other clients. The salmon tartare was presented with chips which is a bit weird for a french restaurant. The duck confit was TINY. One waiter (I think his name was Hippolyte?) was very good and tried as much as he could to limit the damage. The others ones were clueless.

Delicious food, however, was very crowded on Memorial Day and would probably have made sense to have their advertised garden seating open by summer.  Edit to review: after looking at my bank info, I saw that the tip I left was changed, adding about 4-5 dollars more than I put down myself. The reason I noticed was because I accidently left my wallet at home, so I cashapped my fiance to use his card, and only tipped up to the exact amount in the account. When they added on the tip, it over withdrew his card. Not happy about this at all, and positive that my tip and the total that I wrote was not misread. No way you misread two different numbers.
Lovely quiet  place with a great atmosphere.  The staff was very ackmidating to all of us

Staff is good, food a bit disappointing. Oysters are fresh and various which is one of the reasons for a higher rating. As far as food, definitely more mediocre. I'm not being mean, it's just not impressive and selection is more to the poor side. I have had brunch here; its is more a 3.5 or even a 4 out of 5 but for its main appeal it definitely needs work.

My favorite place for French bistro in Brooklyn. Fantastic oysters. ($1 oyster happy hour) and the most adorable back yard for when the weather is nice. Highly recommend the gnochhi, duck, and asparagus.
Consistent good that's good not great.  Friendly staff and airy ambiance.  Backyard is very nice.

Excellent happy hour, $1 oysters and super flattering lighting. I've only been early evening/late afternoons so I haven't seen it when it's wildly crowded.  This is my go to when I just want to chat with a friend and be in a cozy setting.
Great for brunch!

(Translated by Google) Excellent eggs Benedict at a reasonable price. The place seemed popular and crowded but we could easily have a table, thanks to a clever reservation system that warns when the table is available and allows to walk around the neighborhood during the wait. I highly recommend !  (Original) Excellents oeufs Benedict à un prix raisonnable. L'endroit semblait apprécié et il y avait du monde mais nous avons facilement pu avoir une table, grâce à un astucieux système de réservation qui prévient quand la table est disponible et permet de se promener dans le quartier pendant l'attente. Je recommande vivement !
Do it.
Quiet and classy, can't wait for their garden to open up. I am a big fan of their food. Staff are friendly and timely with food and drinks.

Cute, cozy brunch spot. Waited 20 minutes for a table but it was worth it! Food is well-made, portions aren’t too big or small. Wait staff is very polite, nice, courteous. Great place to chill with friends
Went there for brunch and the food and service was excellent

I had the chicken and waffles. Waffle's were ok. Chicken was a bit dry. Not on my top list to return friendly staff.

Great drinks. Very cute neighborhood bistro.
Service and food are both impeccable!
Can be a bit pricy for the hood but the food and atmosphere are perfect, and there are deals to be had if you look. Authentic gritty stylish Nice/South of France feel and taste.

The restaurant ambience is relax and romantic, when we first entered we were greeted and asked where did we want to sit. I think that was really thoughtful and made us feel as though our comfort is of the utmost importance. The staff was very friendly and kept checking in on how we were doing, the food was amazing I ordered the mominette burger with fries yummy. My husband ordered the seafood pasta he said it was so good, he never finishes his food when we go out but his plate was empty. I recommend this restaurant.
That beer tartar was soo good!! What a pleasant surprise

Attended on a whim with a best friend for brunch. Did not have to wait more than 10 minutes. The Bloody Mary was one of the best I've had in quite some time. I got the Eggs de Parme which were eggs Benedict with prosciutto and melted gruyere. Simply delightful. The service was great, with the servers working as a team. It was just the start to the day we needed.

Well...quite deceived about this restaurant... If you are French, look for another place. Portions are really small (I never seen oysters that tiny, the duck confit was for kids). The steak wasn't good. Only the wine and the escargots saved a bit the thing (even if there was too many onions in the escargots' sauce). This is just too much money for a very regular quality food. Service was great though, the waiter was really nice.

I made reservation online and when I called to inform that me and my friends will be few minutes late, person who picked up the phone said that there is no reservation on my name. I had confirmation number and she said she don’t need it and I have to wait for the table 30-40 minutes. This was a waste of my time. Don’t book online!!!!
Hey guys!!! This place is really nice!!! I ordered an onion soup and the Camembert Cheese... OMG everything was so good!!! The place and yr he attention is really nice... I'll be back.... Thanks
Food (burger, avocado toast) was meh definitely not French Patio seems beautiful but opens in May
Everything was great! The customer was great and the food, omg! So delicious! I highly recommend.
Delicious food, enjoyed going with friends for Sunday Brunch, quick service and the food all tasted amazing. Thank you!
Pleasant staff,loud room, good food fair prices

Fantastic oysters. The reason for my poor review is due to having the absolute worst Duck Confit. For the amount we paid for dinner I was blown away by how small and overcooked my meal was. There couldn't have been more than 2oz of charred meat on the dish. It was paired with half a cherry tomato. The other half was on my friends plate. Pretty disappointing to say the least

(Translated by Google) The best French restaurant in New York. Always nice, great food and great cocktails. Vibe charming and relaxed.  (Original) Le meilleur résto Francais à New York. Toujours sympas, tres bonne cuisine et des cocktails supèrbes. Vibe charmant et relaxé.
Quality and value.
Used to go here at least once a week a few years back.  Always a good brunch with steak frites and Bloody Mary
Cozy little spot
Awesome food, great service and amazing ambiance!
Mominette was just nearly a hit. Baked camembert was a bit small and the chutney was bland, gnocchi was nothing special. Duck confit was good though.
Great space and food
Great authentic French food and a wonderful vibe
Came for brunch and was underwhelmed. Basically nothing to eat if you're vegan.
This was a great spot for a cozy kind of date. Food and wine were both good, though a touch small. Still, we left satisfied.
Please please change the brunch music. It does not fit.
Wonderful place. Love the food and ambiance. Service is warm and friendly. Would recommend for cozy dinner or private event in the backyard.
Fresh french feat

Came here on a Sunday afternoon for brunch, service was great with being seated right away and orders taken. Food selection for brunch was cute. Ordered eggs Benny, eggs parm, and Mac and cheese.
